graph TD
    Request(New Schema Version Submitted) --> SubjectCheck{Does Subject exist?}
    
    SubjectCheck -->|No| RegisterNew[Register as Version 1 / Schema ID assigned]
    SubjectCheck -->|Yes| FetchRule{Read Subject Compatibility Rule}
    
    FetchRule -->|NONE| SaveSchema[Accept and Register New Version]
    
    FetchRule -->|BACKWARD| BackwardCheck{"Can new schema parse data written by latest version?"}
    BackwardCheck -->|Yes| SaveSchema
    BackwardCheck -->|No| RejectSchema[Reject registration / Return 409 Conflict]
    
    FetchRule -->|FORWARD| ForwardCheck{"Can latest schema parse data written by new version?"}
    ForwardCheck -->|Yes| SaveSchema
    ForwardCheck -->|No| RejectSchema
    
    FetchRule -->|FULL| FullCheck{"Is schema both BACKWARD and FORWARD compatible?"}
    FullCheck -->|Yes| SaveSchema
    FullCheck -->|No| RejectSchema
    
    SaveSchema --> Success(Return new Schema ID to Client)
    RejectSchema --> Error(Throw SerializationException / Client write fails)

    style FetchRule fill:#ff9,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style SaveSchema fill:#bfb,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
    style RejectSchema fill:#fbb,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px
